  DLS

dls is an terminal based universal open.

What does it mean ? 
I don't know. Have you a better traduction ? :)

It allow to use only one command instead of:
- ls
- less ($PAGER or less)
- gnome-open (need to improve this)
- vi ($EDITOR or vi)
- tar -t[jz]
- {bz|z}cat

usage:
 `dls` -> ls
 `dls -` or `... | dls` -> less
 `dls ...` -> if folder then ls else if text? then less else open end end
 `dls -e ...` -> if folder then ls else if test? then vim else open end end
 `dls -p ...` -> if folder then ls | less else if text? then less else open end end
 `dls -p -e ...` -> if folder then ls | less else if text? then vim else open end end
